Commentary: Faheem Ashraf starts with a length ball, outside off, bit of away movement. Zak Crawley taps it to point.
This is on a length and outside off, extra bounce this time. Crawley leaves it alone.
Faheem Ashraf starts with the channel, outside off. Zak is not tempted and again makes a leave.
Length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley punches but finds point.
A bit fuller, outside off. Zak Crawley gets on the front foot and drives it to mid off.
Beaten! Short of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley has a poke and misses. A good start by Pakistan. A maiden to start the proceedings.
Ali serves a full ball on middle. Duckett eases it to mid on.
FOUR! England and Ben Duckett are underway! Ali errs in line a bit. This is full and on the pads. Duckett tickles it away to fine leg for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off. Duckett cuts to the left of point. Good fielding, only a single.
Too wide this time and swings more away. Crawley has nothing to do with it.
Leg bye! Angling on the pads, too straight. Crawley fails to miss and it goes off the pads to square leg. A leg bye.
On a length and on middle. Defended out.
Length ball, outside off, no sharp movement seen yet but Pakistan have been disciplined. Outside off, punched to cover.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Crawley is off the mark! Short in length and outside off. Crawley hangs on the back foot and punches it through point for a boundary.
Makes it to tail in from outside off. Crawley covers his line and keeps it out.
Length and on off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Outside off, length and it is blocked out.
Leg bye! Slanting on the pads, helped off the pads to square leg for a leg bye.
Full and on off, kept out.
On a length and around off. Crawley gets on the front foot and makes a solid defense.
Fuller and around off. Crawley looks to drive but the inward movement generates the inside edge and it goes to mid-wicket.
Two runs! Short of a length and outside off. Crawley bunts it wide of deep square leg for a couple.
Full and on middle, played to mid on.
Around off, pushed through covers for a single.
Short in length and on middle. Crawley drills it but finds mid on.
Short of a length and on middle. Blocked out.
Crawley uses his feet, this is on middle, it is hit to mid-wicket.
An off-cutter from Ashraf, this one doesn't bounce at all and nips back in. Crawley is surprised as he looks to defend and he misses out.
FOUR! Off the middle. Length and on middle. Crawley drives it past mid on and it races into the fence.
Tad full and on off. Crawley keeps it out.
Full and on middle, defended back to the bowler.
On a length and outside off. Ben Duckett defends it to cover.
Full and outside off, pushed to cover.
Angles it across the left-hander. Ben works it to cover.
Length and on middle. Ben Duckett nudges it to square leg.
Good stop by Imam! Short and outside off. Ben Duckett slaps it to point. A maiden for Ali, his first one.
Leg bye! Slanting on the pads on a length. Crawley misses his clip and it goes to square leg for a leg bye.
FOUR! Finds the gap this time! Too much width, outside off and Ben Duckett gets on it, he hits it through point for four.
On middle, defended out.
Short in length and on leg, Ben Duckett clips it through square leg for three more.
Full and on middle. Crawley works it behind square leg for a single.
Full and on off, pushed to mid off. 9 runs off the over.
FOUR! England have started to find boundaries regularly now. Shorter and outside off. Crawley again punches it beautifully through covers for four.
Length and on off. Zak tucks it to mid on.
On a length and on off. Crawley blocks it.
On middle, it is hit to mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Find the gap! Nothing for Pakistan at the moment and even the length is just too easy for England. Either too short or too full. This is the latter, on middle and Ben Duckett clips it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length and on off. Defended out.
Starts with a loopy full ball, outside off. Crawley drives it through covers for two runs. Good thing is there is spin on offer.
Full and outside off. Crawley prods and defends.
Tossed up, outside off. Crawley gets across to sweep but cannot get much past of square leg.
Very full and on off. Crawley hits it back to Ahmed.

OUT! BOWLED! What a moment for the debutant! A dream debut already! What a delivery from the young leggie. This one goes through the gate. A loopy full ball, outside off, a wrong 'un and Crawley fails to read it. He lunges forward to defend it away from the body but the ball spins in, goes through the gap and hits the stumps. A wonderful piece of bowling and Pakistan get the breakthrough. A good start for Abrar Ahmed.
Howout: b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: FOUR! Pope already shows innovation. Very full and on middle. Pope switch hits it past short third man for a boundary. Some way to get off the mark.
On middle, defended out.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler. It hits the stumps on the other side but Mohammad Ali probably didn't get any skin on it.
Full and on off. Kept out.
On middle, Ben Duckett again blocks it.
Tries a slower bouncer on middle. Duckett pulls it to deep mid-wicket for two.
Very full and on middle. Duckett hits nicely straight down but Ali gets a big hand on it.
This is way outside off, driven to cover.
Full and on middle, Pope nudges it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! Too full and on middle. Duckett sweeps it past mid-wicket for four.
FOUR! This time through the air. Tossed up on middle. Duckett slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket and in the gap for four more.
On middle, swept to deep square leg for one.
Outside off, Pope bunts it to square leg for one. Pope wants another run but is sent back quickly.
Too straight and on middle. Pope flicks it through mid-wicket for easy two.
On a length and around off. Pope punches it to mid on and calls for a quick single. A shy at the bowler's end but Pope was in.
FOUR! Ali needs to get better with his line. This is short and on middle, sits nicely and Duckett stays back to pull through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short again, pulled to deep square leg for one.
On middle, this is pulled behind square on the leg side for a couple.
On off, kept out.
Floated, full and outside off. Duckett looks to sweep but misses it completely.
Flights it full and on off, swept to square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on middle. Pope skips down and nudges it to mid-wicket.
A slower full ball on off. Pope watchfully keeps it out.
Tossed up on off. Pope blocks it off the front foot.
Zahid Mahmood starts with a full ball, outside off, swept through square leg for one. It was hit in the air and Imam-ul-Haq at short leg gets hit on his right ankle. He needs a bit of assistance.
Full and outside off, turning away. Pope stays back to block it out.
Zahid Mahmood goes quicker, outside off, this one again turns away. Pope prods to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. That was close to the stumps.
Beaten yet again! Tossed up on leg, this one lands and turns away. Pope is beaten all ends up as he looks to defend.

Ollie Pope is given LBW but he refers it upstairs. To the naked eye it looks like there is some glove on it. Yes, the players have already taken their position as they see the replay. Tossed up on middle, slower through the air. Pope looks to reverse sweep but gets his on the gloves. Ollie Pope survives.
On middle. Pope reverse hits it past point for a couple of runs.
A juicy full toss on middle, Duckett sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Pope knocks it through cover for a single.
Flatter and around off. Duckett looks to reverse sweep now but misses as the ball turns away.

Three runs! Tossed up on middle. Duckett sweeps but gets a top edge to deep square leg. It flies in the air but falls just in front of the fielder there. It bounces and turns away, making the fielder wrong footed but he reacts quickly to get up, rush back and flick it back near the ropes. Three runs.
FOUR! Connected well! On middle. Pope skips down and clips it past mid on for four runs.
Shorter and on off. Pope uses his feet and reverse sweeps it to square leg for one. Not an orthodox shot from Pope.
Two runs. Tossed up on middle. Pope again uses his feet to reverse hit it past point for a couple of runs. Busy on the pitch.
Floated on off. Pope drives through covers for a brace.
Too full and on middle, Pope nudges it wide of mid on for a single.
Another sweep! On middle, swept to deep square leg for one.
Full and outside off, driven to cover for a single.
Too full, quicker and around off. Duckett mistimes his sweep and it rolls back on the deck. 7 runs off it, 17 off last two.
Shorter and on off. Pope punches it through cover for a single.
Flighted ball on middle. Duckett sweeps it to deep square leg for a single. The 50-stand is up.
On middle, drilled to long on for a single.
FOUR! It is sweep or reverse sweep from Duckett till now. They have done well to see out spin. Ahmed is a bit short though here. Duckett reverse hits it through covers for a boundary.
Flatter and on off. Duckett blocks it out.
FOUR! That is hit hard! Floated outside off. Duckett reverse sweeps it again through covers, in the vacant space for four more.
FOUR! Runs keep on coming. 100 up! Tossed up on middle. Pope reverse sweeps it through point for yet another boundary.
Around off, pushed through covers for a single.

Tossed up on middle. Duckett laps it away. Babar Azam from first slips anticipates it well and runs across quickly but is not that quick to stop the ball. Two runs at fine leg. That is fifty for Duckett! He is in a fine form. A good show from him so far.
SIX! BANG! Floated on middle. Duckett slogs it hard over mid-wicket for a biggie. First of the game.
FOUR! Spinners are leaking runs. Time for Babar Azam to put his mind on work. Shorter and outside off. Duckett slaps it through covers, hard and in the gap for four.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket for a single. 18 runs off the over.

Duckett is given LBW and after a conversation with his partner, Pope, he takes the review. That looks very close. UltraEdge shows that it has HIT THE GLOVE. The bat hits the ground at that time but the third umpire stays with his decision, it is gloves first. Too full, quicker and around middle and leg. Duckett looks to sweep but seems to miss and gets hit on the pads. The replay later shows it was gloves first. Duckett survives this time.
On middle, kept out.
On the pads, nudged to mid-wicket.
Down the leg side. Duckett paddles it to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Tossed up on middle. Duckett looks to flick but gets a leading edge back to the bowler.

OUT! LBW! THREE REDS! A brilliant review from Babar Azam and he finally gets a decision to his favour. Second wicket for the debutant. Ahmed bowls it flat and on middle, slower in the air. Duckett tries to sweep but misses and gets pinged on the pads. An appeal for LBW but it looked like pitching out of the line. Babar Azam thinks and in the dying seconds takes the review. No bat there and the Ball Tracking shows three reds on it. Duckett goes after a fine innings.
Howout: lbw b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Full and on middle, driven to cover.
Short and down leg, this one stays low and turns back in. Pope mistimes his pull back on the deck.
FOUR! Pope continues to play shots! Too full and outside off, it is hit through covers for a boundary.
On middle, kept out.
Full and outside off, driven through covers for a single.
Shorter and outside off, left alone.
Short and outside off. Pope cuts it through point for a brace.
Short again, outside off, Pope slaps it through cover for one.
Root is off the mark! Tossed up, outside off, punched to covers for one.
Quicker, outside off. Pope looks to push but the ball tails in and takes the inside edge.
On middle, Pope stays back and defends.
Better from Ahmed. Showing good discipline on his debut match. On middle, kept out.
Flatter and on middle. Root flicks it through square leg for a couple.
Floated full and on middle, nudged to short leg.
Tossed up on middle. Root prods to defend, it drifts away before helding up, takes the outside edge past first slip for one.
Flatter and on off. Blocked out.
Slightly short and on middle. Pope clips it past mid-wicket. The fielder from square leg covers a lot of ground and saves a single.
On off, driven to long off for one.
Loopy ball on middle. Root nudges it to square leg for one.
On middle, kept out.
Shorter and on middle. Pope bunts it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Tosses it up, outside off. Pope comes down the pitch and eases it through covers for a single.
Waits for the ball to turn on the pads, it is flicked to square leg for one.
Tossed up, drifting on leg. Pope reverse sweeps it to point.
Nawaz starts with a full ball on middle. Defended out.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for a single.
Outside off, pushed to point.
Fuller and around off. Pope reverse sweeps it past point for a couple of runs. Poor fielding there.
FOUR LEG BYES! Outside off. Pope looks to reverse hit but misses. It hits his arms and goes past the keeper to the third man fence.
Flatter and outside off, punched to Nawaz.

OUT! LBW! A long and agonizing wait for Root but he has to go. Abrar Ahmed again convinces his captain to take an LBW decision upstairs. Might be just pitching out. No bat clearly so it all depends on the Ball Tracking. THREE REDS. Once again, fantastic review from Pakistan. Abrar Ahmed has his third wicket. What a delivery again. This one lands on leg and turns back in. Joe Root waits on the back foot to punch it away but gets rapped on the back foot. An appeal and the finger stays down. The review took time to load but eventually ended in Pakistan's favour.
Howout: lbw b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Full and on off, defended out.
Flatter and outside off. Brook punches it through covers for a single.
Shorter and on middle, punched to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Brook doesn't take much time to hit one away! Shorter and on middle. Brook pulls it over mid on for a boundary. 150 up!
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
Full and on middle. Pope defends on the front foot.
Excellent from Pope! Fifty for him! A quick one from him! Full and on middle, drilled to mid on for a sharp single.
Very full and on middle. Brook dead bats it.
Angles a full ball on middle. Brook defends it out.
Tossed up on middle. Brook rocks back and defends it out.
Shorter and outside off, Pope strokes it to point for one.
Tossed up on middle. Brook defends on the back foot.
Around off. Brook punches it to point.
Drifting this one on off. Brook picks it up and defends.
Full and on off. Brook drives it hard but straight to cover.
On middle, quicker. Brook blocks it out.
Tad short and on middle. Pope pulls it past mid-wicket for a brace.
Full and on middle, played back to the bowler.
FOUR! A full toss and Pope takes it well as he hits it through mid-wicket for a boundary. In the gap for four.
Fuller and on middle, Pope uses his feet as he eases it to mid on for one.
On off, pushed to mid off.
JUST OVER! Fuller and around off. Brook comes down the track and drives on the up, slices it over the leaping extra cover fielder for a couple.
On the pads, clipped to deep square leg for a couple.
On off, kept out.
Flatter and on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.

OUT! TAKEN! just at the stroke of Lunch, Pope goes and he is livid with himself. Ahmed continues to flourish on his debut. Floats one on middle. Pope looks to reverse sweep but gets a top edge to point where Abdullah Shafique takes a simple catch.
Howout: c Abdullah Shafique b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Flatter and on middle. Blocked out.
On middle, kept out.
Another solid defense from Brook.
Tossed up on middle. Brook prods and defends.
Flatter and on midde. Brook again defends it out.
Shorter and outside off. Brook cuts it through point and wide of deep cover for a couple.
Tossed up on off, Brook steps forward and works it to point.
Angling on leg, punched straight to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle. Stokes rocks back and blocks it.
Full and on off. Stokes uses his feet to negotiate it out.
A googly, outside off. Stokes keeps it out.
Full and on off. Stokes is off the mark as he reverse sweeps it to deep point for one.

OUT! HIGH IN THE AIR AND IS TAKEN! Five-fer for Ahmed. What a brilliant start to his career! The Pakistani players are all around the youngster as they celebrate the milestone. What a moment for him. Single-handedly kept England on the back foot. Ahmed tosses it up, outside off, it turns away. Brook tries to loft it high past mid off but toe ends his shot, it goes more off the outer half of the bat and high to mid off. Mohammad Nawaz takes the skier there before tumbling on the ground.
Howout: c Mohammad Nawaz b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: On off. Jacks blocks it out.
Flatter and on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, Stokes makes room and punches it to cover.

Tossed up, outside off and it spins in. Stokes prods across to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads as he tries to defend with his bat across. That looked outside the line. Babar Azam is riding his luck as he takes the review. Ultra Edge shows no bat, that is actually very tight to call as the bat and pad were very close. The third umpire stays with the on-field decision and it remains not out. Anyways, it is pitching outside the line.
Full and on off, Stokes reverse hits it past point for three runs.
Tossed up, outside off. Jacks splices his defense to point.
Full, slanting on middle. Jacks gets forward to defend.
Full and on off. Blocked out.
FOUR! Good shot! Angles a full ball on middle, it is swept to deep square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off. Stokes lofts it, again not timed well and there was a fielder standing at mid off who tracks back but it goes over. Two runs. Brave shot.
FOUR! Well played! Tad short, outside off. Stokes slaps it through covers for four more.
Full, outside off and a leggie. Stokes keeps it out.
Tossed up, outside off, turning in. Stokes rocks back and defends it out. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Tossed up, outside off, spinning away. Jacks looks to push but misses.
Flat, around off. Jacks punches it to cover.
Tossed up on off. Jacks prods to defend.
first run after the break. Shorter and outside off. Jacks punches it through covers for a single.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
This one spins in sharply on middle. Blocked out.
On the pads, clipped to square leg for a single.
Fuller and on leg, eased to long on for a single.
Too full and sliding on the pads. Jacks misses his sweep and gets hit on the pads.
Full and outside off, driven to the left of cover. Good stop.
Flatter and outside off. Jacks punches it to cover.
Full and outside off, driven wide of covers for a single.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
This is full and on middle, Jacks sweeps it to fine leg for a couple.
Two more as Jacks hits it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Full and on off, pushed straight to the left of mid off.
Flatter and outside off. Jacks drives on the up but in the vacant cover region for a single.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Full and on off. Jacks leans and defends.
FOUR! Good shot! Fuller and on middle. Jacks sweeps it fine past square leg for a boundary.
Outside off, Jacks reverse sweeps it to point.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle. Jacks gets on the front foot to defend.
Bye! Short on middle, a googly. Jacks looks to cut but misses, he fails to read and the ball goes over the middle pole and to fine leg for a bye.
Tossed up, outside off, kept out.
Flatter and outside off, Jacks punches off the back foot to sweeper cover for one.
A full toss and it is eased to long on for one more.
SIX! BANG! What a shot! Fuller and on middle. Jacks controls his loft well as he hits it over long off for a biggie. 200 up!
On off, punched straight to cover.
On off, kept out.
Very full and on off. Stokes blocks it out.
On the pads. Stokes looks to pull but gets a under edge onto the pads and to third man for a single.
Tossed up, angling on middle. Blocked.
Tad short and on off. Jacks bunts it to mid-wicket.
Three leg byes! Down the leg side. Jacks looks to pull but gloves it past the keeper and to fine leg for three runs.
A googly on middle. Stokes strokes it to point for one.
Flat and around off. Defended out.
This is down the leg side. Stokes follows it and works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and spinning on middle. Stokes hits it to cover.
Full and this is worked to long on for a single.
On off, kept out.
Loopy ball on middle, Jacks bunts it to mid-wicket.
SIX! Stokes hits one now! Pressure on Ahmed! Tossed up on off. Stokes comes down the track and smashes it down to long on for a biggie. Pre-meditated shot.
On leg, pushed straight to mid-wicket.
FOUR NOW! Stokes changing gears now. A loopy ball, outside off. Stokes charges down again as he lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
On the pads, hit to mid-wicket.

This is a googly, full and on the pads. Stokes misses his sweep and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW and the finger stays down. That pitched outside the line however Babar Azam is convinced by his fellow players to take it upstairs. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracking shows it pitched way, way outside leg. Review lost.
Googly again on middle, kept out.
SIX! Boundaries are coming now for England! Nawaz floats it full and on off. Jacks gets low and smacks it over long on for a six.
Outside off, Jacks punches it to deep cover for a single.
On middle, turning in, flicked to mid-wicket for one.
Full and on off, played back to the bowler.
Another solid defense from Jacks.
Flatter and outside off. Jacks punches it to deep cover. A misfield and two runs are taken.
Full and on leg, Stokes keeps it out.
On the pads again, Stokes tucks it to short leg.

OUT! TIMBER! Another one for Abrar! He continues to live a dream! Stokes didn't pick it at all. What a delivery and Stokes has his mouth open as the ball hits the stumps. Tossed up. This one lands on leg and spins away sharply. The length was perfect. Stokes is drawn forward to defend but does so inside the line and beats him on the outside edge. It goes past the blade and hits the stumps.
Howout: b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Tossed up, outside off. Robinson blocks it out.
Full and on off. Defended.
On off. Robinson uses his feet to keep it out.
Shorter and on off, punched to long off for a single.
Outside off. Robinson comes down the track to block.
Angles a full ball on off. Defended out.
This one lands on off and spins away. Robinson is squared up as he looks to defend. The extra bounce saves him there.
Full and on middle. Robinson defends it out.
Flatter, quicker and on off. Robinson pushes it to cover. Jacks wants a single but is sent back.
Outside off, blocked out.
Flatter and on leg. Jacks leans and chips it to mid-wicket. Luckily, the ball falls short of the man at mid-wicket.
On middle, stays low and Jacks blocks it out.
Tossed up, outside off, swept to deep square leg for two.

OUT! LBW! THAT LOOKED PLUMB! Jacks sents it upstairs though. Is this the seventh wicket for Ahmed? Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracking shows it is umpire's call on wickets hitting. That means Ahmed has his seventh wicket now. WOW! Ahmed flights it full and on off, it lands and spins away. Jacks looks to slog-sweep but misses and gets hit on the back pad. England retain the review but lose the final known batter. What a day Abrar is having.
Howout: lbw b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Googly, outside off. Wood prods and defends.
Flatter and on middle, defended.
Slightly shorter, this lands and turns away. Ollie Robinson initially thought of pulling it but then defends.
Flatter and on off, Ollie Robinson keeps it out.
Fires it on middle, blocked.
On the stumps, defended.
A single as this is played to point.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Off the inside edge! Tossed up on off, this one lands and comes back in. Wood looks to drive but it goes off the inside edge past the leg pole and down to the fine leg fence.
On middle, blocked.
FOUR! Pulled away! Slightly short and asking to be hit! This is hit over mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, Wood gets right behind the line and defends.
Shorter and on off, Wood pushes it to covers.
Ollie Robinson straightaway goes after Zahid Mahmood! He steps out but yorks himself. He jams it out to mid on.
FOUR! This time gets hold of it! The slog sweep is out and he nails it over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary. All these are handy runs for England.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally, a wicket for a Pakistan bowler other than Abrar Ahmed! One thing is for sure now, he won't be taking a ten-fer. This is tossed up nicely on middle, a lot slower. Ollie Robinson goes for the slog sweep again, this one flies off the top edge towards mid on. Mohammad Nawaz takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Mohammad Nawaz b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! Two in two for Zahid Mahmood and England are 9 down now! Very uncharacteristic of Leach. He looks to play the switch hit but this is bowled slower yet again and on the stumps. Leach is through his shot and it hits the stumps. Can England be bowled under 250 now?
Howout: b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: No hat-trick for Zahid! On middle, this is defended.
FOUR! Just a run away from the 250-run mark then! On off, James Anderson plays the reverse sweep, gets on top of the bounce and hits it down to the third man fence.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Wood looks to cut but is beaten.
On off, defended.
250 up for England! Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On the stumps, kept out.
On middle, this lands and turns back in. Mark Wood looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but going down leg.
Shorter and on middle, this is pushed to cover.
On middle, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Up and over! Mark Wood steps out, he gets to the pitch of the ball, hits it over cover with the turn for a boundary.
FOUR! Through mid-wicket now! Floats it up on middle, Wood goes for the slog sweep, it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Really well bowled! Floats it up on off, this lands and turns away. Wood is beaten as he tries to defend.
FOUR! Put away! This is poor bowling! This is short and on middle, asking to be hit, Wood pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Just about misses the off pole! This is slower again and it is outside off. Wood looks to play the slog sweep but misses.
Fuller and outside off, Anderson pushes at it, it goes off the outside edge down towards deep point for one.
The last pair continues to frustrate Pakistan! On middle, Wood looks to sweep, it goes off the pad and towards fine leg for two.
Big swing and a miss! Outside off, Wood looks to go over the leg side but misses.
FOUR! Just wide of the fielder at deep mid on! Wood steps out, he gets to the pitch of it and hits it wide of the fielder at mid on who is slightly deep. A boundary.
FOUR! Over the fielder! Wood is dealing in boundaries! Outside off, this is slapped over cover for another boundary. 300 now looks possible.
FOUR! Shorter and around off, Wood looks to cut, this goes off the top edge, lands just short of Imam-ul-Haq who lets it through. Boundary.
On middle, this is swept through square leg for one.
Outside off, this is carved out towards deep point for one.
On middle, this is pushed to cover.

OUT! TIMBER! Pakistan finally get the last wicket! This is tossed up, slower and on off, James Anderson looks to play the switch hit but is done in by the dip n the delivery, it hits thew stumps. ENGLAND ARE ALL OUT FOR 281!
Howout: b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: Solid from Abdullah Shafique! Length and on middle, he defends it out.
On off, Abdullah Shafique gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
On the stumps, kept out.
Angled into the pads, Abdullah Shafique works it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but misses, it hits the pad and rolls on the leg side.
Abdullah Shafique and Pakistan are underway! On middle, Abdullah Shafique looks to defend, it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
FOUR! Hammered! This is shorter and outside off, Abdullah Shafique rocks back and slams it through covers for a boundary.
Flatter and on middle, this is defended.
That is a beauty! This is tossed up on off, it lands and turns away. Abdullah Shafique is beaten as he tries to defend.
Slightly shorter again and just around off, Abdullah Shafique cuts but finds point.
Slower through the air and outside off, left alone.
Slows it up and lands it around off, this is cut but to point.
Good length and on off, kept out.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Imam waited for a long time, had a long chat with his partner but then decides to walk back! A duck for Imam and England strike early. Just what they would have wanted. This is a back of a length delivery, just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq looks to push at it, there is some extra bounce, it takes the outside edge and the keeper does the rest. England celebrate. Imam walks down to his partner but does not review it and that is the right decision as Ultra Edge shows a spike.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b James Anderson

Commentary: Good length and on off, Azam defends it solidly.
Three more! Azam is off the mark! Shorter and on off, he stands tall and pushes it through covers for three.
Anderson rolls his fingers on this one, it is fuller, Shafique plays it to covers.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
FOUR! A little too short and Azam puts it away! This is short and outside off, Azam cuts it past point and this races away to the fence.

That is a beauty! This is slowed up, it lands on middle and then turns away sharply. Azam looks to defend but is beaten. Leach is really getting the ball to grip and turn here. Also, some extra bounce.
This is not where he would want to bowl! This is short and around off, Azam cuts it past point for three.
Really well left! Flatter and around off, this lands and turns away. Abdullah Shafique sees that and lets it be.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique defends it.
On the the stumps, this is kept out nicely.
Bangs it in short and on off, Azam guides it to point.
Shorter and on off, Azam plays it through covers for one.
Angled into the pads, Abdullah Shafique works it through square leg for no runs.
Bangs it short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique ducks under it.
Another one on the shorter side, not played at.
End of a lively over from Mark Wood! He goes short again, Abdullah Shafique lets it go over him.
Flatter and on middle, blocked.
On the stumps, kept out.
Floats it up on off, this is kept out nicely.
On middle, Azam looks to defend, it goes off the inner half through square leg for no runs.
Lovely! Slows it up, lands it on off, this pitches and turns away, Azam looks to defend, it goes off the outer half to point.
On middle, blocked.
Bangs it short again and on the body, Abdullah Shafique guides it to point.
Angled into the pads, Abdullah Shafique looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.

FOUR! Top edge and down to the fine leg fence! This is banged in short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique looks to pull, this flies off the top edge and goes over the leg slip fielder and into the fine leg fence.
Good pace! Short and on middle, Abdullah Shafique arches and looks to play the upper cut but misses it totally.
Another short one and on middle, Abdullah Shafique ducks under it.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
Leach has found his length and line! On middle, this is kept out.
On the stumps, kept out.
FOUR! Risky shot but gets the boundary! This is shorter and quite close to off pole. Azam cuts, he gets it fine on the off side for a boundary.
Floats it up on off, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.
On off, Azam pushes it to cover again.
On the shorter side and on middle from around the wicket. Blocked.
Bangs it short and on the body, Abdullah Shafique nudges it around the corner for one.
Babar was in two minds there! Short and on middle, Azam was looking to duck intially but then defends it.
On off, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Up and over! Safe shot! Shorter and outside off, Azam cuts it over point and this races away to the fence.
Floats it up on middle, kept out.
On middle, Abdullah Shafique is solid in defense.
On the stumps again, defended.
Flighted ball on off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and keeps it out.
On the stumps, it is kept out.
Fuller and on off, AS pushes it to covers. Tidy stuff from Leach!
FOUR! Sheer timing! Fuller and on off, Babar Azam shows the full face of the bat and times it past the bowler and down to the long off fence.
More runs! Fuller and on middle, Azam works it through mid-wicket for two.
Right off the middle but to the fielder! Fuller and on off, Azam strokes it to covers.
On the shorter side yet again, Azam guides it to point.
Bangs it short yet again and on the body, Azam ducks under it.
FOUR! Outstanding! Shorter and on off, Azam stands tall and just guides it past point. That was not a very bad ball but such is the class of Azam. Lovely.
Abdullah Shafique steps out and hits it to mid off.
On middle, defended.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
FOUR! Finds the gap this time! Uses his feet again, gets to the pitch of it and strokes it wide of mid off for a boundary.
On middle, blocked.
On the stumps now, it is kept out.
On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
FOUR! Good effort but in vain! On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side. The square leg fielder gives it a chase, dives and looks to push it back but touches the ropes in the process.
Tossed up on off, blocked.
On the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Azam flicks but to short leg.
FOUR! The fifty is up in style! Lovely shot! Shorter and on off, this is pushed past the cover fielder and into the fence.
Outside off, left alone.
On the stumps, blocked.

A loud appeal but turned down! Pope is pretty sure that has taken the edge and England review! OUT! ULTRA EDGE SHOWS A SPIKE! England get a timely wicket as this partnership was going along really well! Jack Leach delivers! This is tossed up around off, it lands and turns away. It takes the faintest of edges. Pope takes it and appeals. The finger stays down but England use the review to good use. England still trail over 230.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Jack Leach

On off, blocked.

On the stumps, defended.

Shorter and around off, Saud pushes it through point and takes three.

SIX! This is a massive hit! This is given a lot of air, it is full and around off, Azam heaves it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
On middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to short leg.
Shorter and on off, Shakeel pushes it through covers and takes two.
On middle, defended.
On off, it is kept out.
On the stumps again, defended.

Fifty for Azam! The skipper leading from the front yet again! On middle, he works it towards mid-wicket for one. He scored a ton in the first innings of the last game and his side would love one here from him.
On middle, this is worked to mid on.
Saud Shakeel steps out, he gets a little too close to the pitch of the ball and swings, it goes off the inner half towards square leg.
Floats it up on off, defended.
Steps out but the length is shortened, this is pushed to mid on.
On middle, defended.

FOUR! Up and over! Lovely use of the feet yet again, gets to the pitch of the ball and lofts it with the turn over the mid-wicket fielder. 100 up for Pakistan.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! The slog sweep comes out now, this is nailed too, it goes for another boundary in the mid-wicket region. 50-run stand up between the two. Handy one but needs to go on.
Flatter and outside off, this one goes on with the angle. Azam looks to push at it but is beaten.

FOUR! SHOT! All class there! Shorter and around off, Saud waits and then pushes it past point for a boundary. The wicket seems a lot better to bat on today, at least so far.
Back of a length and on off, defended.

Back of a length and on off, defended.
FOUR! The sweep is nailed! On the pads, Saud hits it through square leg. Nobody in the deep there and hence, it is a safe shot. Saud moves into the 40s.
Now follows the boundary with a run as this is worked towards square leg.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Azam goes back and works it through mid-wicket for two.
FOUR! Whipped away! Picked the length really quickly! This is fractionally short! Azam goes back and hits it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Runs coming quickly this morning.
On middle, defended.
That is a beauty! First real sign of the ball turning this morning! Floats it up on off, this lands and spins away. Azam is beaten as he tries to defend.
Good length and on off, defended.

A direct hit and Saud was gone! On the pads, Saud works it towards square leg and wants a run. He is sent back. The fielder gets to the ball, picks it up and has a shy but misses. Had he hit, Saud was a goner. He had given up. The fielder could have taken a little more time. Zak Crawley was the man!
On off, Saud defends.
Down the leg side, Saud looks to flick but misses.
FOUR! That is sheer timing! Wonderful! Length and on off, Saud just strokes it on the up through covers and this one races away to the fence.

Three more! Yet again picks the length early, this is slightly short, Azam works it through mid-wicket for three.

FOUR! Fifty for Saud! He has looked really good in this innings and especially this morning. Important knock but needs to go on! He gets there with a lovely sweep, it is on middle, he plays it through square leg for a boundary.
Good length and on off, blocked.

OUT! TIMBER! Where has this guy been? He was probably England's best bowler in the first game, he comes on to bowl his first after 34 overs and strikes on the very second ball. Breaks the stand which just looked unbreakable. That is a gem of a delivery. This lands outside off, it pitches and jags back in sharply. Azam looks to drive but it sneaks past the inside edge and hits the stumps. England will now feel back in it. Huge wicket here. Can this open the floodgates? Pakistan still trail by another 139 runs!
Howout: b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Ollie Robinson is getting the ball to move now! This is fuller and around off, this is pushed to mid on.
Good length and on off, defended.
Well fielded! Fuller and on off, Rizwan strokes it towards mid off. The fielder dives to hs right and stops it.
Tossed up on off, defended.
On the stumps, defended.
On the pads, Saud works it to square leg.

On middle, blocked.

Goes wide of the crease and angles it into off, defended. Rizwan is still to get off the mark. England keeping the pressure on him.
Rizwan can't just get off the mark at the moment! Shorter and around off, Rizwan waits and then guides it to point. He hit that well but to the fielder.
Length and on off, blocked. Really good stuff from Ollie Robinson!
A surprise short ball, Saud though gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through square leg for one.
Outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
That is a beauty! Cuts Rizwan into half! This lands outside off and jags back in sharply. Rizwan lunges forward to defend but it goes past the inside edge. This is an outstanding spell from Ollie.
On off, blocked.

This is brilliant from England! Just giving nothing away at the moment! On middle, Saud defends it.

NOT OUT! That is clipping the leg pole! England do not lose their review! Wood from around the wicket bowls it full and on the pads. Saud looks to drive but misses, it hits the pad and rolls on the off side. A leg bye taken as the bowler is appealing. Turned down. Wood convinces his skipper to go for the review. Replays show that it remains umpire's call.
Another dot! Outside off, left alone.
On middle, Saud works it to mid-wicket.
Length and on off, Saud plays it to covers.

Angled into middle, Rizwan gets right behind the line and defends it.
On the stumps, blocked.

FOUR! That is a beautiful stroke! Very delightful! It was not a half volley, it was behind a fuller length, outside off, Rizwan makes use of the width and strokes it through covers. He is finally off the mark and that shot will give him a lot of confidence.
On middle, this is blocked.
On the pads, Saud works it to mid-wicket.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Works it with the turn to mid-wicket.
FOUR! That is a lovely shot! Very nicely controlled! Steps out, gets to the pitch of it and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a superb, superb catch from James Anderson! Absoluetly brilliant and England have both the overnight batters back in the hut! The tidy bowling all this while has paid off. Not sure though if Shakeel played the right shot there. He got a boundary on the last ball, looks to step out and go over mid on this time. The length is dragged back a little by Leach. He ends up hitting it high up in the air behind mid on. James Anderson runs back, he has a fielder running towards him from deep mid-wicket but calls for it, stretches out and takes it nicely. England back into the game. Pakistan still trail by 123 runs.
Howout: c James Anderson b Jack Leach

That is a top but to end! A yorker on middle, Salman jams it out towards md off. Pakistan have gone into a shell here.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to cover.
Floats it up on off, defended.
On middle, Rizwan defends.
FOUR! Up and over! Mohammad Rizwan looks to break the shackles! Steps out and hits it over the mid on fielder for a boundary.

OUT! TIMBER! That is a beauty from Jack Leach! England now on top in this game! Another big wicket in this session. Mohammad Rizwan never looked that comfortable and now falls. He has not had the series he would have liked so far. This is tossed up, it angles into the leg pole. It lands and then holds its line. Mohammad Rizwan looks to work it on the leg side but is done in by the turn. It goes past his bat and hits the stumps. Pakistan still trail by above 100. Half the side back in the hut for them.
Howout: b Jack Leach

Howout: c Ollie Robinson b Jack Leach

Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! England are all over Pakistan now! The last batting pair for the hosts has been broken! England can now think of a really good lead! This is a soft, soft dismissal! Tossed up on off, Agha Salman looks to drive, this probably holds off the surface. It goes off the inner half and straight to short mid-wicket where it is taken by Stokes.
Howout: c Ben Stokes b Joe Root

On the stumps, kept out again.
This lands around leg and goes on with the angle. Mohammad Ali looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but turned down.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Root has two in the over and Pakistan are 8 down now! What a collapse this is! This is flatter, it lands on middle and goes on with the angle. Ali looks to defend, it takes the outside edge, it hits the hand of the keeper and lobs kindly to the slip fielder where it is taken by Zak Crawley!
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Joe Root

He takes a review along with him too.

Takes one now as he works it through square leg. Now Abrar Ahmed has two balls to play out.
On middle, this is kept out.
Half an appeal but turned down! This is flatter and outside off, Abrar Ahmed looks to cut but misses to get hit on the pads. The impact was well outside off.
Floats it up on off, Faheem defends.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Floats it up on off, kept out.

This lands outside off and turns back in. Faheem Ashraf looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the pads.There was actually an inside edge.
On off, blocked.

Wood goes short again and on middle, Abrar looks to play the upper cut but misses. A full one coming up now?
