OUT! TAKEN! Straight to the fielder! Mark Wood can't believe it! England bag a lead of 79! Angled into the pads, Faheem Ashraf flicks it uppishly and straight to the man at deep square leg. Ben Duckett takes it easily. Pakistan HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 202!
Howout: c Ben Duckett b Mark Wood

Commentary: England and Zak Crawley are underway! Length and on off, Zak looks to defend, it goes off the outer half towards point. The fielder dives over the ball. Two taken.
Good length and on off, Zak pushes it to covers.
Around off, this is guided towards point for one.
This one comes back in but the line is a little too straight. Ben Duckett looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On middle, this is pulled towards md-wicket.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and outside off, Zak Crawley looks to drive but it goes off the inner half towards mid off.
Good length and on off, Zak pushes it to covers.
Crawley gives Ashraf the charge, it is a length ball outside off, left alone.
Length and outside off, Zak Crawley looks to drive but it goes off the inner half to covers.
Finds the fielder! Length and on off, this is pushed but to covers.
Slightly shorter, this one stays a touch low, Crawley looks to pull but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and outside off, Ben Duckett strokes it but to covers.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
FOUR! Off the mark in style! Really not sure if starting with two pacers is the right move. This is short and outside off, it is cut over point for a boundary. Poor delivery and put away!
FOUR! Put away! Yet again, too full and too wide and Duckett hammers it through covers for another boundary. Two in two.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
Two dots in a row! On off, this is again played to mid off. Probably we will be seeing a spinner from this end.
Good length and on off, Zak defends.
Length and on off, Zak pushes it to covers.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
That is a good delivery! A yorker on off, it is jammed out to mid off.

OUT! RUN OUT! Zak Crawley is well short! Abrar Ahmed can do no wrong! He is the one with the direct hit but why did Zak Crawley run there! He was well short and there never seemed to be a run in that. On middle, this is pushed to mid on. Crawley calls for one. Abrar Ahmed runs towards the ball, picks it up, takes a second to aim and then underarms it onto the stumps at the bowler's end. It is taken upstairs and replays show Zak Crawley is short! Perfect start for Pakistan!
Howout: run out (Abrar Ahmed)

Commentary: That stays low! Outside off, on a length. Duckett looks to drive but is beaten.
Jacks comes down the wicket straight away, this is shortish and on middle, it is worked down to fine leg for one.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Length and on off, blocked.
A slower one on middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and outside off, this stays a touch low. Duckett looks to cut but misses.
Three more! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for three.
Good length and on off, blocked.
FOUR! Slightly short and Ben Duckett pounces on it! He pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On middle, length, this is pushed back to the bowler.
On the pads, this is flicked but to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Duckett pushes it to mid off.
Length and on off, Ben guides it to point.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket, bad bounce for the fielder and he does not stop it. Two taken.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On the pads, Ben Duckett plays the paddle scoop down towards fine leg for two.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.

OUT! TIMBER! Abrar Ahmed comes on and strikes! His 8th wicket of the game and the move to send Will Jacks up the order does not work! This is tossed up outside off, a lot slower. Will Jacks looks to heave it on the leg side but is a touch early in the stroke. He misses, the ball turns back in and hits the stumps. England two down now.
Howout: b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Well fielded! Fuller and on off, this is pushed towards mid off. The fielder dives to his left and stops it.
On the bounce! A slower one around off, Ben Duckett hits it on the up but it lands short of mid off.
Nicely played! Around off, Duckett waits and then guides it wide of deep point for two.
Fuller and on off, this is driven towards cover. The fielder dives to his right and makes a half stop. A single.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Another one on a length and around off, kept out.
On off, tossed up, this is hit to covers.
On off, this is again played to cover.
Drags his length back, this lands on middle and turns back in. Duckett looks to defend, it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, blocked.
A loud appeal from the bowler but an inside edge! On middle, Root looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On middle, Root works it to mid-wicket.
Good length and on middle, this is pushed to mid on.
FOUR! Short ball and hammered! Duckett pulls it over the mid-wicket fielder and into the fence.
Good length and on off, blocked.
Full and outside off, Duckett jams it out towards point.
Slightly shorter, this one skids through. Duckett thinks of pulling it at first but then defends.
Fuller and on off, this is driven firmly towards cover. The fielder sticks one hand out and makes a half stop. It goes towards mid off and hence, a single.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed down to long off for one.
On middle, this is pushed towards the right of mid-wicket who dives and saves a run.
Gives it air and lands it on off, blocked.
On off, kept out.
On the pads, this is swept through square leg for one.
FOUR! Hammered! Length and outside off, this is slapped through covers for a boundary.
Width on offer again outside off, Duckett slams it but to covers.
On off, this is kept out.
Around off, Duckett guides it to point.
Back of a length and on off, this is guided to point.
Around off, this is played to point.
Full and on middle. Blocked out.
Flat and outside off, Root punches it to cover.
Angling on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Touch short and outside off. Root cuts it to point for one.
Slower one on the pads, turning away. Kept out.
This is full and on middle, clipped to mid-wicket for a single.
Length and on middle, Duckett tucks it to mid-wicket.
Short in length and on off, dabbed to point.
Length ball on off, guided to point once again.
Slanting on the pads, nudged to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Well played! Length ball, outside off. Root uses the width and places it wide of first slip to third man for four.
This one nips back in on off. Blocked out.

A big shout for LBW but looked outside the line. This is full and angling around off from 'round the wicket. Duckett reverse hits but misses and gets hit on the pads. The Pakistani players get together before taking it upstairs. The impact saves Duckett as it was umpire's call. That spun a long way but still not enough for Abrar to get his second wicket. Not out it is.
On middle, swept to deep square leg for a couple.
One more as Duckett sweeps it to deep square leg.
Tossed up on middle. Defended on the front foot.
This one drifts in on off. Root prods and blocks.
Tossed up on middle. Root plays with soft hands behind square leg for a brace.
In the gap for three runs. Flatter and outside off. Duckett punches it through covers.
Three more! Outside off, Root opens the face of the bat and dabs it to third man.
Two now! On the pads, Duckett helps it behind square on the leg side for a brace.
This one turns on middle. Duckett tucks it to square leg for one.
Slides it full and on middle, nudged to square leg for one.
On middle, tucked to mid on.
Flatter and on middle. Root bunts it to square leg.
Floats it on middle. Defended out.
Tossed up on off, turning in. Root prods to defend but some gloves on it. It hits the pads and falls just wide of short leg. Actually, there was no gloves.
On middle, kept out.
Fuller and outside off. Root defends on the front foot.
Almost chopped on. Shorter and around off, googly. Root mistimes his cut to point.
Full and on off. Duckett works it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up on off. Root punches it through cover for a single.
Full and on off, eased to long on for a single.
Full and on middle. Blocked out again.
Too full, quick and on middle. Root leans and blocks.
FOUR! Really well played! Full and on middle. Root laps it to fine leg. The fielder from square leg runs and slides but to no avail. A boundary to end the over.
Tossed up, around off. Duckett steps across to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but Pakistan do not take the review. Impact was outside off.
Too full and on off, Duckett sweeps it to deep square leg for a single. The lead is now 150.
Tossed up on middle, Root keeps it out on the leg side.
A leggie, outside off, pushed to cover.
This is full and on middle. Root comes down the track and nudges it to deep square leg for a couple of quick runs.
Fuller and on middle. Root rocks back and defends it out.
Shorter and on middle. Duckett pulls it to deep square leg in the gap for two.
Tossed up on off, nudged to mid-wicket.
Fifty for Duckett! Back-to-back fifty for Duckett! He is having a really good series. Tossed up on middle, this is swept behind square leg for one.
Around off, punched to cover.
Outside off, tucked to mid-wicket. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. The back up fails to collect it cleanly and another run is taken.
On off, Root blocks on the front foot.
Angling on off, swept to deep square leg for one.

OUT! WHAT A CATCH! Abrar tosses it up, outside off. Root closes the face of the bat as he tries to paddle it, it goes more off the top edge, aerially and to short leg. Abdullah Shafique there was moving away so had to stretch, he pulls his left-hand out, gets his fingers underneath and takes an absolutely brilliant catch. The umpires take it upstairs to check if the catch is clean and the replay shows Abdullah Shafique did really well to keep it away from the ground. A moment of brilliance there and Abrar Ahmed gets his second wicket.
Howout: c Abdullah Shafique b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: On middle, pushed to mid on.
Tossed up on off, pushed to cover.
Fuller and on off, Brooks taps it to point for a single.
On middle, swept to deep square leg for one.
Slower one on off, pushed to mid on.
Flatter and outside off, Duckett sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Kept out.
Goes very full and on middle. Harry blocks it out.
Tossed up on off, Brooks drops it to cover.
This is very full and on off. Brook skips down and drives it firmly to cover who misfields it to mid off and allows a single.
Brook didn't pick that at all. Short and on middle, a googly. Brook wants to cut but gets deceived. He gets some part of the bat and goes to square leg for one.
On off, swept to deep square leg for one.
Flatter and outside off, punched to cover.
On off, kept out.
Full and on off. Brook prods and defends.
Slow and turning away. Brook slaps it to cover.
On the pads, clipped to square leg for one.
Angles a full ball on middle, tucked to square leg.
Tossed up on off. Brook defends on the front foot.
This is outside off. Brook uses his feet to keep it out.
Slants a full ball on middle. Brook stays back and defends.
Angling around off. Brook again defends.
Tossed up, outside off, spins in. Duckett looks to sweep but gloves it away. The fielder at leg slip is wide than the normal position and hence it races to fine leg for three runs.
Outside off, punched to mid off.
Full and on middle. Brook lunges forward and defend.
Tossed up on off, Brook steps across and dead bats it.
Quicker one on middle. Blocked out.
Floated on middle. Brook leans and defends. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Tossed up on middle. Duckett punches it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on middle. Duckett works it to long on for a single.
awaz serves a full toss on the pads. Brook looks to flick but misses. That was going down.
Tossed up on middle. Brook on the front foot, defends.
This is full and outside off. Brook skips down and pushes it through cover for a single.
Around off, flat and it is pushed to mid on.
Tossed up, on off, drifting in. Brook stays back and pushes it to point.
FOUR! Brook releases the pressure, he is finding it difficult to play Abrar. Full and outside off. Brook comes down and hammers it past the bowler for four.
Shorter and on off. Brook looks to pull but mistimes, the ball lands wide of the mid on fielder.
A single as this is flicked to square leg.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Goes wide outside off, this is a googly. Brook looks to drive but inside edges it to square leg for one.
Tossed up on off. Defended out.
Flatter and around off. Brook defends it out.
Outside off, pushed to cover-point for a single.
A single as this is eased down to long on.
Good fielding in the end! On middle, nudged to mid-wicket where the fielder dives to his right and stops. He fumbles a bit and the batters look for a quick single but eventually denies it.
On middle, kept out.
On middle, this is hit to square leg for one.
On off, kept out.
Flat and on middle. Blocked out.
Tad short and outside off, pulled to long on for a single.
On the pads, Duckett sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Slows it up on off. Brook leans and blocks it out.
Loopy ball on middle. Duckett nudges it to square leg for a single.
Shorter, googly and around off. Brook works it to the right of mid on for one.
Outside off. Duckett gets his front foot across to defend.
On middle, this is pushed to long on for a single.
on off, kept out.
FOUR! Good shot! Flatter and outside off. Brook waits, opens the face of the bat and steers it past first slip to third man for a boundary.
Touch short and on middle. Duckett gets low and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Around off, worked through covers for one.
Flighted full and on middle. Duckett reverse sweeps it through covers for a brace.
On middle, nudged through square leg for one.
Flatter and on middle, kept out.
FOUR! Short and punished. This is around off, it is pulled away to long on for a boundary.
DROPPED! Babar Azam drops an absolute dolly. Abrar Ahmed drops it short and on middle. Duckett with gentle hands tries to pull but hits straight to mid-wicket where Babar Azam drops a sitter.
On middle, nudged to square leg for a single.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Too full and around off. Brook leans and blocks it out.
Slower, flat and on middle, bunted to mid-wicket.
A googly, full and on middle. Brook defends.
Shorter and spinning on middle, tucked to mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, guided through point for a brace.
Tossed up on off. Brook hangs back and defends.
Way outside off, left alone.
Flatter and outside off, Brook punches it off the back foot and to cover.
Top edge but safe! Tossed up on off, a googly. Brook looks to sweep but mistimes it high and behind square leg where it falls safely. One.
SIX! Sees short and punishes it straightaway! On middle. Brook rocks back and pulls it high and over long on for a biggie.
FOUR! Brook pulls it again, this time not off the middle but again there is no fielder at deep mid-wicket and it rolls away to the fence.
Full and on off, pushed to long off for a single.
BEATEN! Absolute beauty. A googly from around the wicket, fuller and outside off. Duckett prods to defend but misses.
Drags his length ball, outside off, kept out.
A leggie outside off. Duckett draws forward to defend.
Flatter and outside off, punched through covers for a single.
This one spins from outside off. Duckett stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Goes full and outside off, spins away. Brook looks to drive but outside edges it to third man for two.
A single as this is hit to long off.
Three runs! Tossed up on middle, turning in. Duckett sweeps it fine to fine leg for three runs.
Much better from Zahid. He needs to this line and length. Tossed up, outside off, Brook is drawn forward to defend but is beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Duckett continues to get boundaries! Flatter and outside off. Duckett reverse hits it to third man. The fielder runs across, slides and gets a hand on it but in vain.

OUT! BOWLED! Abrar Ahmed gets his 10th wicket in the match. What a moment for the debutant. Not his best of deliveries but he will take it anyhow. Even he knows it was not a wicket-taking delivery. Lucky for Abrar but not for Duckett who goes after a well made 79. Ahmed serves a flat ball, outside off, angling in, it lands and doesn't bounce at all. Duckett tries to pull but is deceived by the lack of bounce and the ball hits the off pole.
Howout: b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Flat and on middle. Pope nudges it through mid-wicket for a couple.
On middle, kept out on the leg side.
Fuller and outside off, driven to cover.
A googly on off. Pope defends on the front foot.
Around off, pushed through cover for one.
Flighted on off, Pope pushes it to long off for one.
Another single as this is hit to long off.
Flatter and outside off. Pope works it through cover for one more.
Outside off, cut to deep cover for a brace.
Tossed up on off. Brook defends on the front foot.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Tossed up on middle. Pope skips down and drills it to mid on.
On middle, blocked out.
Flatter and on middle. Pope comes down the track as he looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW but not given. Pakistan think to review but they don't.

OUT! RUN OUT! Another one goes! This is really good from Pakistan! Flatter and way outside off. Pope slaps it to the left of cover. Pope calls for a run and rushes but Harry Brook after taking a couple of steps changes his decision. Pope turns from halfway mark but till then Mohammad Nawaz throws it to the keeper who whips the bails off. Pope dives but he fails to drag his bat. Clearly out. England lead by 234 runs now.
Howout: run out (Mohammad Nawaz / Mohammad Rizwan)

Commentary: Flighted on middle. Stokes prods and defends.
Full and on middle. Brook prods and defends.
On middle, kept out.
Around off, defended on the front foot.
Outside off, Brook works it to cover for one.
Angling on middle, flicked to square leg for one.
Shorter and on off, Brook punches it to cover for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off, Brook drives it to cover for a single.
On middle, kept out.
Outside off, left alone.
Shorter and around off. Stokes keeps it out.
Tossed up, outside off, angling in. Stokes tries to reverse hit but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but again the impact looked out of the line.
On middle, eased to long on for a single.
This is full and way outside off. Stokes paddles it to square leg for a single.
Flatter and outside off, punched to cover for a single.
Loopy ball, outside off. Stokes leans to defend but gets an outside edge wide of first slip.
Full and outside off, Stokes reverse sweeps it to point for a single.
Fifty for Brook! He too is having a wonderful series. Full of runs. Need to stay out there though. Full and on middle. Brook nudges it to mid-wicket for easy couple.
Tossed up on middle. Brook keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle. Stokes works it to square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Blocked out.
Flatter and on middle. Brook punches off the back foot to mid on.
Floats one on off, blocked out.
Fuller and on middle, blocked out.
FOUR! belted down! Flighted on middle. Brook lofts it to long on for a boundary. He looks comfortable now.
Flatter and on off, Stokes drills it to long on for one.
Bowls it way outside leg, no spin and Brook lets it go.
Fuller and on middle, Brook plays it to the bolwer.
Down the leg side. Brook sweeps but finds short fine leg.
Down the leg side from around the wicket. Brook reaches to the pitch of the ball and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Way down leg. Brook misses his sweep.
Full and on middle. Stokes skips down and eases it to long on for a single.
A googly, around off. Brook sees it out well.
FOUR! Good shot! Drifts one, around off. Brook plays it late past point for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
Shorter and on middle. Brook stands tall and blocks.
Tossed up on middle, played to point for a single.
FOUR! Brook sweeps this down the leg side delivery past short fine leg for a boundary.
On leg, flicked to square leg.
This is way down the leg side. Brook misses his sweep.
FOUR! Beautiful shot from Brook! Best shot of the day! Tossed up, down the leg side. Brook makes room, comes down and goes inside-out through covers for a boundary.
Down leg, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Shorter and around off, turning in. Stokes makes room and punches on the up to mid off.
Shorter and outside off, cut to point.
On middle, played back to the bowler.
Shorter and outside off, Brook punches it through covers for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Stokes drops it to cover for a single.
Quicker one on middle. Brook blocks.
Way outside off, Brook works it past point for a single.
On a length and on middle. Brook blocks out.
Length ball, slanting on middle. Brook flicks it to deep square leg for a single. A no ball as Mohammad Ali has overstepped.
On a length and around off. Stokes is happy to defend.
Length and outside off, tapped to point for a quick single.
This is full and on middle. Brook prods and dead bats it.
Full and on off. Brook gets his head down and blocks it out.
A length and on middle. Brook defends solidly again.
Angling on the pads, flicked to square leg.
Tossed up on off, Stokes skips down to keep it out.
Tossed up, around off. Stokes reverse sweeps it to deep point for a single.
Outside off, it is punched through covers for a single.
Touch short and on middle. Stokes pulls it to deep mid-wicket for two more.
Flatter and outside off, Stokes taps it to point for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Stokes reverse hits it to point for a single.
Shorter and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Around off, pushed to covers for a single. 200 up!
On middle, this is hit to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter and on leg, punched to mid on for a quick single.
Tossed up on off, Brook keeps it out. That will be Stumps on Day 2.
Starts with a fuller ball, around off. Stokes defends in front of him.
Tossed up on middle. Stokes leans and blocks it out.
Slower through the air, fuller and it is the one which spins back in. Stokes defends it well.
First runs of Day 3! Tossed up on leg, Stokes reverse sweeps it through point for a couple of runs.
Too much width, outside off and it is cut through point for one.
Touch fuller and around middle. Brook prods and blocks it out.
This is full and outside off. Stokes comes down the track and pushes it to mid off.
Now stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads, it is clipped to deep square leg for a couple more.
Beaten! Ali hits the deck hard, outside off on a length. Stokes looks to whip it away but misses. Ali needs to use more variations with pitch doing nothing for the seamers.
Outside off, punched to cover.
On a length and on off, Stokes uses his feet and taps it to mid off for a single. The umpire has a word with Stokes as he runs on the pitch.
Flat and on off, kept out.
Slightly short and on middle. Stokes stays back and tucks it just wide of short leg and for a run.
A slider, full and on middle. Brook defends.
Tossed up on middle. Brook comes down the pitch to negotiate it.

A huge appeal for caught behind and the finger stays down. Mohammad Rizwan looks convinced and he asks Babar Azam to take it upstairs. Ultra Edge shows a flat line, no bat involved and Stokes will continue with his merry way. Abrar Ahmed slides one down the leg side and spins back in. Brook steps across to sweep but seems to miss. Pakistan burn their review.
On leg, Brook keeps it out.
A length ball, outside off, pushed to cover.
No ball! Outside off again. Stokes slaps it firmly but finds the man at cover. A no ball as Ali overstepped.
Stokes looking to go hard. This is full and outside off. Stokes looks to smash but toe ends it to mid off.
Three runs! Very full and on leg, it is flicked wide of deep square leg for three runs.
QUICK SINGLE! Length and outside off. Brook drops it to cover for a single.
FOUR! Stokes taking the charge now. Short and on off. Stokes skips down to pull, doesn't time well but powers it away to deep mid-wicket for four.
Length and on off, a cutter and Stokes defends.
FOUR! Brook with a boundary now! Fuller and on off. Brook lofts it over mid off for four.
A googly, around off. Brook defends it out.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, slower and around off. Brook prods to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Picks the length very quickly. Touch short and Brook is quick on the back foot as he pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Around off, pushed to cover. A misfield and a single is taken.
FOUR! Boundaries coming in each over now. Poor bowling rather than power. This is on a length and tailing on the pads. Brook tickles it to fine leg for four.
Length and on off, punched to cover.
This is full and around off, Brook drives it to cover.
On off, defended out.
This is outside off. Brook blocks again.
Flatter and outside off. Brook works it to cover for a single.
Tossed up on middle. Brook defends on the front foot.
FOUR! Brook moves into the 90s! Tossed up, outside off. Brook slogs it hard over mid-wicket for one bounce and into the fence.
A googly, quicker and around off. Brook does well to cut it to point. He played really late there.
Loopy ball, outside off, Brook taps it to point.
FOUR! Second in the over! Brook moves to 97. He is not letting the loose balls go. Shorter and on off, this is pulled over mid on for a boundary.
Flatter and on middle. Brook keeps it out.
Full and on middle, stays low. Stokes pushes it to long on for one.
Touch short and on off, turning away. Brook rocks back and blocks.
Tossed up, outside off, pushed to cover.
This is full and on middle. Brook defends it out.
Angles a full ball on the pads, kept out.

FOUR! Hundred for Brook! He was itching to go big and finally he does. His second century in this series. This player is a serious talent. Stokes from the other end celebrates like a proud father. Superb knock from Brook. Touch short and on middle, it is pulled high and over deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Down the leg side, swept to square leg.
SIX! Stokes goes big! England is full control. Loopy ball on off. Stokes dances down the track and thumps it straight down for a biggie.
Slower one on middle, knocked to cover for one.
Outside off, guided to point for a run.
Tossed up, outside off. Stokes looks to defend but this turns away and takes the outside edge, it goes away from first slip, past his hands and to third man for three runs.
On middle, blocked out.
Flatter, slower and outside off, stays low. Stokes looks to pull but misses.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally someone not known as Abrar Ahmed takes the wicket in this innings.. A much needed one and Pakistan break the 101-run stand. Nawaz bowls it touch short and around off, stays low again. Stokes shuffles across and gets indie the line to slog-sweep but hits more of the higher part of the bat and to deep square leg. Mohammad Ali runs to his left, misjudges the flight for a while but takes a brilliant catch diving forward.
Howout: c Mohammad Ali b Mohammad Nawaz

Commentary: Around middle, kept out.
On the pads, flicked through square leg for a couple.
Shorter and outside off, cut to point.
Outside off again, Robinson works it through covers for one.

OUT! TIMBER! Robinson goes now. Abrar Ahmed gets his fourth wicket. He bowls it flat, straight and around middle and leg. Robinson comes down the track to heave but the ball beats him on the inside edge and goes past his pads to hit the stumps.
Howout: b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Tossed up on off, Wood blocks it.
Quicker one on middle. Wood rocks back and defends it out.
This is outside off, left alone.
A googly, around off. Wood reads and blocks it out.
This is slow from Abrar, outside off and spins away. Wood feels for it and looks to defend but misses. Mohammad Rizwan catches and appeals but the replay later shows there was nothing on it.
Tossed up on off. Brook skips down and bunts it to long on for a couple.
On middle, worked to mid on for one.
Slants it full and on off. Defended out.
Flatter and on middle. Wood leans and blocks it.
Shorter and on middle, nudged to square leg for a single.
Slants on middle, tucked to deep square leg for one.
Full and on off, Brook defends on the front foot.
Flatter, outside off, turning away. Brook works it to point for one.
Outside off, Wood guides it to backward point.
FOUR! Wood doesn't miss out. Loopy ball, around off. Wood slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
A googly, around off. Wood lunges and defends it out.
Shorter and outside off, cut to cover for a quick single.
Full and on off, defended.
On off, Wood defends solidly again.
Slants a full ball, down leg and spins back in. Wood looks to sweep but misses. An appeal but it is pitching outside leg.
On middle, kept out.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! The change works for Pakistan! Flatter, slower in the air and outside off, turning a bit away as well. Wood stays back and has a gentle poke at it only to get an outside edge to first slip where Babar Azam takes a low catch. The lead is now of 349 runs.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: A proper leggie, outside off and turning in. Leach prods to defend and nudges it past short leg.
Too full and on middle. Brook defends on the front foot.
A loopy ball on leg. Brook blocks again.
Flat and outside off, punched to point for one.
A googly, loppy ball, around middle. This one sharply turns away. Leach lunges forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge. It flies to first slip but there was no bat. Beautifully bowled.
On off, kept out.
Superb from Ahmed! Full and on middle. Leach does well to defend.
Loopy ball on middle. Brook blocks.

OUT! TAKEN! The centurion goes. Well played Brook! The lead is now of 350. Zahid Mahmood serves a loopy ball, around off, spins away. Brook looks to slog-sweep but toe ends his shot. It goes high and to deep square leg where Saud Shakeel holds onto it. End of a really good innings from Brook.
Howout: c Saud Shakeel b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: FOUR! Outside off, James Anderson reverse sweeps it past first slip and to third man for four.
On middle, blocked out.

OUT! LBW! An LBW appeal and up goes the finger. James Anderson takes the review but the players are already walking off as they know the result. Tossed up, around middle, not much turn and James Anderson plays the wrong line as he looks to sweep but gets hit on the pads. The replay shows there was no bat and three reds on Ball Tracking. Out it is. England end with 275.
Howout: lbw b Zahid Mahmood

Commentary: This is full and outside off. Abdullah Shafique leans and pushes it to cover.
Shorter and on the hips, Abdullah Shafique tickles it behind square leg for a single. Pakistan are away in the chase.
Ollie Robinson serves a full ball on off, it is pushed to cover.
On a length and on middle. Rizwan defends it out.
On a length and on off. Rizwan defends in front of him.
On a length and around off. Rizwan is drawn forward as he blocks it out.
Tossed up on off, not much turn and Abdullah Shafique defends on the front foot.
Fuller and on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends in front of his pads.
That was an absolute beauty! Tossed up, around off. Abdullah Shafique rocks back to defend, he gets an outside edge and it hits Ollie Pope on his thigh before lobbing over first slip for a single.
Tossed up, outside off, stays low this one. Rizwan looks to sweep but misses.
Fuller and outside off. Rizwan defends it out.
Rizwan uses his feet! This is full and on middle, it is hit past mid on for two.
On middle, this is hit to square leg for one.
On a length and on middle. Rizwan keeps it out.
Length ball, around off, much better line and length. Tight! Rizwan gets his bat down to defend.
Drags his length ball and keeps it around off. Rizwan again defends it.
Ollie Robinson keeps the same length, around off. Rizwan works it to cover.
Outside off, punched to cover.
Too full and on middle, angling in. Defended on the front foot.
Fuller and around off, Abdullah Shafique drills it to the right of mid-wicket, a misfield and a couple is taken.
Tossed up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique steps across to defend.
Flatter and outside off. Left alone.
Slants a full ball on off. Abdullah Shafique prods and defends.
Four dots to end the over! Full and on off, kept out.
Short in length and on middle. Rizwan tucks it to deep square leg for a brace.
Full and outside off, pushed to cover.
On a length and outside off. Rizwan dabs it to point for a single.
A bouncer, around off. Abdullah Shafique bends his back and lets it go.
On a length and on middle. Blocked out.
Short of a length and outside off. Abdullah Shafique steps across to defend.

Good work from Anderson! Tossed up, outside off. Rizwan comes down the track and smashes it to long off. It slows down and James Anderson gives a chase. He slides near the ropes and does well to save a single. Excellent work there.
SIX! That is right off the middle. Tossed up on middle, slanting in. Abdullah Shafique skips down and lofts it straight down the ground for a biggie.
Quicker and around off. Abdullah Shafique keeps it out.
On off, defended out again.
Full and outside off, spins away. Abdullah Shafique prods and works it to point.
FOUR! Good shot! 13 runs off the over. Too full and angling on middle. Abdullah Shafique flicks it through mid-wicket and it races into the fence.
Very full and on middle. Rizwan looks to sweep but misses. An appeal but not a full-hearted one.
Tossed up on off. Rizwan gets his front foot across to defend.
FOUR! Loosener and hit away! Down the leg side, it is swept behind square on the leg side four.
Slanting on leg. Rizwan pads it away.
Fuller and across outside off. Rizwan drives it through covers for a brace.
FOUR! It is raining boundaries at the moment! Good start for Pakistan! Shorter and outside off. Rizwan cuts it through point for one more four.
FOUR! Intent! Leach is struggling a bit with his length. This is outside off. Abdullah Shafique cuts it past point for another boundary.
Too full and on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends on the front foot.
Much better! Tossed up, around off, spins away after landing. Abdullah Shafique prods to defend but misses.
Fuller and on off. It is defended.
On off, kept out.
Good delivery! Fuller and around off. Abdullah Shafique lunges forward and defends.
On middle, kept out.
A single as this is hit through cover.
A loopy ball on middle. Abdullah Shafique on the front foot defends.
Angling on leg, nudged to deep square leg for one.
Too full and on leg, Rizwan sweeps it behind square leg for one.
Floated on the pads. Abdullah Shafique nudges it to short leg.
Very full and slanting on middle. Rizwan stays back to block.
Flatter and outside off. Rizwan slaps it through point for a couple of runs.
Outside off, dabbed to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Abdullah Shafique leans and blocks.
This is outside off, left alone.
Flighted on off, Abdullah Shafique defends.
Tad short and outside off, punched to the left of mid off for one.
Floated on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.

Not out it is! This is very full and flat from Root, angling around leg. Abdullah Shafique looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal for LBW but that was pitching outside leg. England look a bit desperate as they want to break this stand and take it upstairs. The replay shows that is outside the line.
Angles a full ball on middle, extra bounce. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
On the pads, tickled to fine leg for one.
On middle, blocked out.
Fuller and on middle. Abdullah Shafique defends on the front foot, it goes of the inside edge to mid-wicket for one.
A single as Rizwan drills it to mid on.
Tossed up on off. Abdullah Shafique prods and defends.
Well bowled! Slants a full ball, around off and makes it to turn away. Abdullah Shafique is drawn forward but is beaten on the outside edge.
This time the line is down the leg side. Abdullah Shafique helps it down past the keeper to fine leg for two more. 50 up!
Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique defends on the front foot.
A length ball, outside off at 141 clicks. Rizwan drops it to cover.
On a length and outside off. Rizwan stays back to defend.

Finally England get the wicket but Mohammad Rizwan confidently reviews it. He thinks there is some bat on it and the replay shows a big deflection on it, a huge inside edge. Short of a length and around off, it was there to be pull but the ball stays low. Mohammad Rizwan gets an inside edge as he looks to pull and gets hit on the pads. Ultra Edge fails to load but a normal replay is enough to make a decision.
On a length and on middle. Blocked out.
Outside off, length and Rizwan defends it out.
Two runs off the over! Full and outside off, it is driven through point. The fielder makes a good stop in the deep.
Tossed up, it lands on off and spins away. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend on the front foot but misses.
Full and on off. Abdullah Shafique gets inside the line this time to block it.
Slows it up on middle. Blocked out.
Fuller and around off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it again.
Flatter and on off. Kept out.
FOUR! There is no stopping to the run flow. Flatter and on middle. Abdullah Shafique sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Outside off, guided through point for a single.
Short and on off. Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms to it.
SIX! BANG! Abdullah Shafique uses the pace, this is short and on middle. It is pulled all the way over deep square leg for a biggie.
Fuller ball, around off, shaping in. Abdullah Shafique prods and inside edges his defensive shot to square leg.
Angling on the pads, bunted to square leg.
On a length and around off. Abdullah Shafique survives as he defends. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
A length ball, around off. Rizwan steps forward to block.
Length ball, angling on middle. Rizwan defends it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Rizwan cuts it through point for two runs.
On a length and on middle. Rizwan keeps it out on the leg side.

OUT! TIMBER! There is the wicket England were looking for. An absolute jaffa from the legend! He has till got it. James Anderson, what a beautiful bowler. Mohammad Rizwan just stands there in disbelief as to how that ball went past his bat. What a delivery. Anderson serves a length ball, this one angling in and then moves away off the deck. Rizwan gets forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge and the ball goes onto hit the off stump. Just what England needed after the break.
Howout: b James Anderson

Commentary: A length ball, outside off. Azam defends on the off side.
A length ball on middle. Shafique defends it on the deck.
Length ball, outside off. Shafique defends on the up and to cover.
Outside off, solidly defended again.
A slower length ball, outside off. Shafique hops and defends.
Ollie Robinson goes back to the stumps, Shafique watchfully defends.
Outside off. Shafique keeps his head down and defends.
On a length and on middle, nips in. Azam nudges it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, sliding down, Azam might have missed his flick here. Ollie Pope fails to flick. Yes, it went off the pads.
On a length and around off. Azam stays back and defends.
Azam is off the mark. Length and on middle, this is clipped to deep square leg for one.
Anderson goes full now on off. Shafique is happy to defend it out.
Length and on middle. Shafique leans and defends.
Length ball, outside off, knocked to cover.
On a length and outside off. Azam punches but straight to cover.
Fuller ball, outside off, Azam keeps it out.
Length ball, outside off. Azam drives it firmly again but finds cover.

OUT! BOWLED! Beauty from Robinson! What a delivery! Ollie Robinson gets Babar Azam for the second time in this game. Babar Azam just like Rizwan is shell-shocked. The big wicket for England. They have really turned up after Lunch. Ask them what they had. Ollie Robinson steams in and serves a length ball, outside off, this one lands and nips back in sharply, might have hit one of the cracks. Babar Azam sees and then shoulders arms to it but the ball deviates and hits the stumps. He just watches the pitch. A late, late movement and Azam has to go now.
Howout: b Ollie Robinson

Commentary: Fuller and on off, defended out.
Full and on middle, nips in. Shafique keeps it out.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
On a length and on middle. Shafique blocks it to mid-wicket.
On a length and around off. Shafique defends with a straight bat.
On a length and outside off, jags in. Shafique watchfully blocks it.
Goes full and on middle. Shafique dead bats it.
Length ball, around off. Defended out.
Welcome run! Length and on off. Saud plays with soft hands and splices it to third man for a single.
Touch fuller and around off. Shafique defends on the front foot.
Full and outside off, defended to cover.
Short and on middle. Shafique gets on his toes to block. A no ball as Ollie has overstepped.
Brave leave from Shafique! Length ball, outside off, this one again nips back in sharply. Shafique shoulders arms. Not far away from the off pole.
Full and on off, Shafique defends.
Around off on a length. Saud defends it well.
On middle, blocked again.
On middle. Saud prods and defends.
Short and on middle. Saud gently pulls it to deep square leg for one.
Full and on middle, eased to mid on.
A length ball on middle, angling in. Shafique is a bit squared up as he defends this.
Full and outside off, Saud away from his body, knocks it to cover.
Fuller and outside off, it is driven to covers.
Short and outside off. Saud lets it go.
On middle, kept out.
Tails in a full ball on middle. Saud stays back to defend it again.
Another solid defense from Saud.
Length ball on middle. Shafique is happy to block everything right now.
An effort ball from Wood as he bends and serves a short ball. Shafique evades it.
Another bouncer and Shafique again ducks.
This one nips back in on middle. Shafique leans and blocks it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Shafique drives it through covers for a single. Pakistan just sucking all the pressure right now.
Wood serves a short ball on leg. Saud sits under it.
Fuller ball on off. Shafique strides forward to defend.
Fuller ball, around off, nips in but Shafique has his line covered.
Well timed! Full and on middle. Shafique flicks it through two short mid-wickets for three runs.
This is outside off, left alone.
Around off, Saud takes a step forward to defend.
A dot to end! Full ball, outside off, pushed to silly mid off.
A loopy ball on middle. Shafique defends on the front foot.
Tossed up on off. Shafique again leans and blocks.
No run.Full ball, slanting on middle. Shafique gets his bat in front of the pads to defend.
On off, kept out.
This is full and on leg. Shafique goes inside-out, fails to middle but clears the cover fielder for a brace.
Slower through the air on middle. Blocked out.
On middle, defended.
This one tails back in from outside off, kept out.
Angled into the pads, this is worked down to fine leg for one.
Good length and on off, blocked.
On off, defended.
Fuller and on middle, Shafique pushes it back towards the bowler, silly mid on dives to his left and stops it.
Flatter and on middle, Shakeel works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! A little too short and hammered away! On middle, Abdullah Shafique rocks back and slams it over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary. That will release a little pressure.
On middle, defended.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed towards cover for one.

PUT DOWN! A very tough chance though. That just needed to stick. You can call that a technical chance! On middle, Shakeel flicks it uppishly, Brook at short leg sticks his right hand out but the ball does not stay in.
On middle, defended.

OUT! TIMBER! Yet again the stumps are hit! That is a beauty of a delivery! The combination of pace and movement gets the better of Abdullah Shafique! This starts around off and comes back in a long way after pitching. Abdullah Shafique looks to defend but it sneaks through the gap between bat and pad and uproots the off pole.
Howout: b Mark Wood

Commentary: Fuller and angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
EDGY FOUR! Imam is off the mark in a streaky manner! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Imam looks to defend, it goes off the outside edge down to the third man fence.
Another one on a length and around off, blocked.
Fuller and on middle, Imam pushes it to mid on.
A single to end then! Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq looks to flick but it goes off the outer half through point for one.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
Floats it up on off, Imam comes forward and blocks it out.
On middle, this is worked towards long on for a couple.
On middle, Imam flicks it to mid-wicket.
On the stumps again, Imam works it to mid-wicket.
On off, defended.
Turn! Lovely delivery! This is tossed up outside off, Saud Shakeel reaches out for it, it lands and then spins away. Saud is beaten as he tries to drive.
The sweep comes out, it goes more off the top edge but lands safe in the square leg region. For one.
On middle, defended.
On the pads, this is worked to square leg.
On the pads, this is nudged around the corner for one.
On the off pole, this is defended solidly.
Pushes this one through and on the pads, Imam works it to short fine leg.
Sees Imam come down the track and shortens the length, it is worked to short fine leg.
Gives this a lot of air and lands it on off, Imam defends.
Two more! Very well fielded! Imam-ul-Haq steps out, he lofts it down the grund towards long on. The fielder runs to his right, dives and keeps it down to two.
On off, blocked.
Imam steps out and pushes it to covers.
Floats it up on off, Saud Shakeel gets right behind the line and blocks.
On off, defended.
Flatter and on off, kept out.
Another one on off, Saud is solid in defense.
Fires this outside off, left alone.
On middle, blocked.
FOUR! Pushed away! Slightly shorter, just outside off, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and pushes it through covers for a boundary.
On off, this is blocked.
On middle, Imam works it towards mid-wicket.
On the pads, Imam flicks it to square leg.
On the pads, Imam works it to square leg.
On the pads, Imam flicks it to short leg.
On middle, defended.
Shorter and around off, Saud cuts it through point and takes two.
Tossed up on off, defended.
FOUR! Cut away! Slightly on the shorter side, Saud rocks back and hammers it through covers for a boundary.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
Pakistan now need exactly 250! Outside off, shorter, this is slapped through covers for one.
Floats it up on off, blocked.
On middle, Shakeel defends.
On middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Imam wanted a run but Saud Shakeel was not interested! On middle, this is nudged on the leg side.
On middle, Imam works it towards square leg again.
Shorter and on middle, blocked.
Short and asking to be hit, Saud slaps it but straight to cover.
Floats it up on middle, Saud is solid in defense.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
Around off, Saud waits and then guides it through point for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, this is played to point.
Floats it up on middle, defended nicely.
On middle, kept out.
Fired in on middle, Shakeel is solid in defense.
On off, Shakeel pushes it to covers.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Up and over! Imam steps out, he gets to the pitch of it and lofts it over the long on fielder for a boundary. Welcome one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Two! Shorter and outside off, this is slapped through covers for two.
On the pads, Saud looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Around off, this is played through point for one.
On off, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Outside off, this is cut through point for one.
On middle, blocked.
On the stumps, kept out.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, blocked.
Around off, this is kept out nicely.
On off, Shakeel pushes it to covers.
On off, this is played to mid off.
A single as this is pushed through covers.
On off, defended.
On the stumps, this is defended too.
Flatter and on off, Shakeel keeps it out.
A single as this is guided through point for one.
around off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Shorter and outside off, Imam looks to cut but is beaten.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to mid-wicket.
Shorter and on middle, Imam pulls it through mid-wicket and takes one.
On the pads, this is worked down to fineleg for one more.
On off, Shakeel pushes it towards cover.
Floats it up on off, this is worked down to long on for one.
On off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Imam nudges it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Imam works it to mid-wicket.
On off, kept out.
Very full and on middle, this is jammed out towards mid off.
A single as this is guided through point.
Two more! On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for two.
A short one, Imam leaves it alone.
Another short one on the body, Imam ducks under it.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through square leg for two.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
On middle, blocked.
FOUR! Cut away! Shorter in length and outside off, Shakeel waits and just guides it through point for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, defended.
FOUR! Up and over! Saud steps out, he gets to the pitch of it and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
Floats it up on off, this is defended.
Floats it up on off, defended.
Imam steps out, the length is shortened, he defends it.
Driven nicely but only one! Fuller and on off, this is hit down towards long off for one.
On middle, defended.
Flatter and on off, this is blocked.
Flatter and on off, Saud plays it to cover.
Two more! On middle, this is worked through square leg for a couple.
FOUR! Hammered down the ground! Stokes is really close and he had no chance! Imam steps out and gets to the pitch of it, he smashes it down the ground to the long off fence.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On middle, blocked.
A single now as this is worked towards mid-wicket.
On the stumps, kept out.
Flatter and on off, Shakeel pushes it to covers.
On off, this is blocked.
Angled into the pads, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket.
On middle, kept out.
A single as this is pushed towards cover.
On middle, this is played towards cover.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Hammered! This is way too short and asking to be hit! Saud Shakeel rocks back and slams it through covers for a boundary.
On off, defended.
On off, Shakeel gets right behind the line of the ball and blocks it.
FOUR! Up and over! Pakistan now need below 200! This is tossed up on off, it is lofted over the mid off fielder and into the fence.
On middle, kept out.
Floats it up on off, this is defended.
On the stumps, defended.
Another one on the stumps, blocked.
Shorter and around off, this is cut through point for one.
Angled into the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
Two more! On the shorter side, this is guided through point for two.
Uses his feet and plays this down to long on for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket for one.
On the stumps, defended.
FOUR! Whipped away! That is a top shot! On middle, this is whipped through mid-wicket for a boundary. This partnership will really be worrying the visitors now.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
FOUR! Beautiful! Inside-out! Shorter and on middle, this is fuller outside off, Imam lifts it over covers and it goes to the fence behind.
On middle, blocked.
On the stumps, kept out.
On middle, Imam gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
Another one on the stumps, blocked.
On off, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.
Shorter and on off, Imam pushes it to covers.
On off, Imam guides it through point for one.

Outside off, Imam guides it towards point and gets to the other end. Fifty for Imam! Not where he usually bats but he is enjoying it. Vital knock too, both for him and his side but he needs to go on. Still a long way to go.
On the pad, Shakeel now works it through square leg for one.
Good length and on off, blocked.
On the pads, Imam flicks but to square leg.
Outside off, Imam guides it towards third man for one.
On middle, defended.
Back of a length and on middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone.
Short ball and this is pulled nicely through square leg for one.
Really good shot but for no runs! Fuller and on off, this is driven but to covers.
On off, defended.
Another one on off, Shakeel gets right behind the line and defends.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
On the stumps, defended.
Fuller and on off, this is driven firmly to one of the three men at covers.
Angled into middle, Imam hangs back and defends it.
Good length and on off, this is pushed to cover.
Quite a funny incident there! As the bowler was about to deliver, Shakeel dropped his bat. Imam then works this one on the pads, through square leg. They take two. Saud ran without his bat there.
Length and on off, blocked.
Good length agian and on off, defended.
Shorter and around off, Saud guides it down to third man and gets to the other end.
Down the leg side, Imam looks to flick but misses. Half an appeal but turned down. Stokes did not review and guess what? ULTRA EDGE SHOWS A SPIKE!
FOUR! Hit firmly! Fuller and outside off, Imam waits and then slams it through point for a boundary.
On middle, defended.
Outside off, left alone. Ollie Robinson has overstepped and hence, it is a no ball.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Another no ball as Ollie Robinson opversteps again! On the stumps, this is defended solidly again.
On middle, Shakeel gets right behind the line and defends it.
On off, this is kept out.
On the stumps, defended solidly.
Gets this one to tail back in a touch from around off, Shakeel pushes it to mid on.
On off, kept out.
On middle, blocked.
Another single! Outside off, Imam guides it down to third man for one.
Goes short again, this is worked down to fine leg and a run is taken.
Another short one, Imam does play the pull shot, it goes through square leg for one.
Around off, this is carved through point for one.
Bangs it short and on middle, Imam ducks under it.
Good length and on off, this is kept out.
Played nicely! Length and outside off, Shakeel guides it towards point and gets to the other end.
Good length and on off, this is guided to point.
That is well fielded! Will lift the spirit of the bowlers so late in the day! Shorter and on off, this is cut but Zak Crawley dives to his left and stops it.
Brilliant in the field again! On the pads, this is worked towards square leg. Jamie Overton the sub dives to his left and stops it.
On the stumps, this is defended.
On middle, this is worked to square leg.
Fifty for Shakeel! He has got off to starts in this series, it is his third fifty but he needs to go on to make it big here. His team needs him too. On middle, this is worked through mid on for one.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a superb catch! Brilliant from Root and the stand that was taking the game away has been broken. This will open the floodgates now for England? They will hope se. This is tossed up outside off, Imam-ul-Haq looks to drive, it goes off the outside edge as the length was not quite right. It goes to the left of Root who takes a sharp catch. Imam can't believe it. England back on top. 164 more needed.
Howout: c Joe Root b Jack Leach

Commentary: Tossed up on off, blocked.
Floats it up on off, defended again.
Loopy ball on off, blocked.
On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, this is whipped but to mid on.
Fuller and on the pad, this is played to mid on.
On off, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.
On middle, Faheem Ashraf defends it.
On off, kept out.
Flatter and on the pads, Saud works it to mid-wicket.
Anther run as this is nudged towards mid-wicket.
On the stumps, kept out.
Shorter and on off, this is pushed to cover.
On off, Shakeel strokes it to covers and takes one.
Gives it a lot of air and lands it on middle, defended.
Flatter and on off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On the pads, Faheem Ashraf works it to mid on.
On middle, Faheem blocks it.
Flatter this time and on middle, kept out.
Really good running! On the pads, this is clipped through square leg. Two taken.
No run.
On off, this is pushed through covers for one.
On the stumps, blocked.
Around off, this is played to cover..
On the stumps yet again, Faheem pushes it to cover.
Outside off, left alone.
On off, defended.
Fires it on middle, kept out.
Angled into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, kept out.
On middle, this is blocked nicely.
Shorter and outside off, this is played through point for one.
Another single as this is pushed through covers.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wickst.
Tossed up on off, this is pushed to cover.
Flighted ball know off, kept out.
On off, defended.
On middle, this is worked to mid on.
On middle, Faheem pushes it to mid on.
On the stumps, Shakeel plays it onto the ground.
From around the wicket, angles it into the off pole. Shakeel gets right behind the line and plays it out.
Shortish and on off, this is pushed to cover.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked to mid on for one.
On the stumps, it is kept out well.
Angled into the stumps, this is kept out.
FOUR! Timed nicely! Fuller and on middle, this is timed nicely down the ground and it races away to the fence.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
Flighted ball on off, this is blocked well.
A single as this is worked with the angle towards mid-wicket.
On the stumps, this is flicked to mid-wicket.
On the stumps, this is blocked.
On the stumps again, this is kept out nicely.
Tossed up on off, this is played through mid-wicket for one.
Another single as this is pushed through cover.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! There is the first wicket for England this morning and it is quite early. Joe Root is the one who gets it and Pakistan have half the side back in the hut and they need another 145 runs. This is tossed up nicely, it lands around off and then turns. Faheem Ashraf pushes at it with hard hands, it goes off the outside edge and it is taken by Zak Crawley at first slip.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Joe Root

Commentary: Length and on off, this is defended.
Another one on the off pole. Saud Shakeel gets right behind the line and defends it.
Angled into the pads, Saud looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls on the leg side. It goes off the pad towards the leg side. Leg bye taken.
On middle, it is blocked.
EDGY FUR! Length and on off, this lands on off, Mohammad Nawaz looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge down to the third man fence for a boundary.
Angled into middle, blocked.
On the stumps, blocked.
Flighted ball on off, Shakeel pushes it to covers.
Slower through the air and on middle, Shakeel defends.
What was the sound? It was probably the bat hitting the ground! Shorter and outside off, Saud looks to cut but this one stays low. It is taken by the keeper in the end.
Floats it up on off, Saud defends it onto the ground.
On middle, defended.
Angled into the pads, this is flicked to mid-wicket. Good from Joe Root, he is varying his pace nicely.
Length and on off, Nawaz pushes it to covers.
Around off, Nawaz plsys it through point and gets to the other end.
Angled into the off pole. Saud gets right behind the line of the ball and blocks.
Angled into the pads, Saud works it to mid-wicket.
Bangs it in on middle, Saud ducks under it.
A yorker on middle, Saud jams it out to mid on.
Out comes the sweep, it is hit well but towards deep square leg for one.
Loopy ball on off, defended.
Angled into the pads, Saud works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on off, Nawaz pushes it to mid off for one.
Another single then! Shorter and around off, this is guided through point for one.
Fires it on off, Nawaz blocks.
Length ball on middle, nudged to square leg.
Serves a bouncer at 143 clicks, dies on its way. Saud sits under and lets it go.
Short ball on middle. Saud gets his bat up and defends on the deck.
Angles a full ball on middle. Shakeel blocks it out.
Slanting on the pads, flicked to square leg for a quick single.
One more run! Length and on the pads. Nawaz clips it behind square leg for one.
Fuller and outside off, driven through point for a single.
Lovely delivery! Tossed up, slow and on middle. Shakeel gets back to defend.
Flighted on middle. Shakeel tucks it past mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Good shot! Floats it full and on middle. Nawaz sweeps it hard through mid-wicket for a boundary.
An arm ball on middle. Nawaz defends.
Three more! Tosses it up on middle. Nawaz paddles it fine to fine leg for three runs.
On middle, blocked out.
On a length and outside off. Nawaz dabs it to third man for one.
Short in length and on off. Shakeel hops and defends.
Length ball on middle. Shakeel keeps it out.
Length ball on middle. Shakeel dead bats it.
Angling on the pads, Shakeel nudges it to square leg.
Fuller and on off, defended to cover.
Serves it outside off but not much spin. Nawaz defends.
Full and on middle, eased down to long on for a single.
Tossed up, outside off, turning in. Shakeel steps across to defend but misses. The catch is taken at short leg but there was no bat.

FOUR! Lucky! Flatter, outside off, spinning in. Shakeel gets his front foot across to sweep, gets a bit of glove and the ball just goes over the stumps and past the keeper to fine leg for four. Leach is getting turn.
A single to end the over as this is hit to mid-wicket.
Starts with a delivery down the leg side. Left alone.
A short ball, outside off. Shakeel looks to pull but misses.
A well-directed bouncer on middle. Shakeel misses his clip and gets hit on the gloves.
Outside off, this is tapped to third man for a single.
A bouncer on middle. Nawaz lets it go.
Around off on a length. Nawaz knocks it to point.
Flighted outside off, Shakeel drives it through cover for a single.
FOUR! Driven firmly! Too full and outside off. Nawaz drives it through covers for a boundary.
Leach keeps it outside off. Nawaz strokes it to cover for one.
Well outside off. Shakeel leans and taps it to the vacant cover region for one.
Tossed up, outside off. Nawaz defends it out.
This one spins in, around off. Nawaz blocks it out.
Full and on off, Shakeel defends, it goes more off the splice to third man for a single.
Length and on middle, blocked out.
Length ball, outside off, bit of movement. Nawaz knocks it to cover.
On middle, another solid block from Nawaz.
On a length and on off. Mohammad Nawaz keeps it out.
BEATEN! Short in length and outside off. Nawaz looks to cut but misses.
Tossed up on off. Shakeel looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Too full and on off. Shakeel prods and defends.
On off, blocked out again.
Floats it way outside off. Shakeel leaves it alone.
Flatter, outside off, slower and Shakeel punches it through covers for a single.
FOUR! Releases the pressure! Floated on middle. Nawaz comes down the track and smashes it down to long on for four. Pakistan need 103 runs now. 250 up!
Length ball, outside off, blocked.
Full ball, outside off, from round the wicket. Shakeel defends.
Length and on off, Saud drops it to point.
On middle, Shakeel gets inside the line and eases it to mid on.
Full and on the pads, nudged wide of mid-wicket for a quick single.
Length ball, slanting in on off, extra bounce on offer. Nawaz defends it out.
Tossed up, outside off, Shakeel pushes it through covers for a single.
FOUR! The target is now under 100. Floated, outside off, too much width and Nawaz slaps it through covers for a boundary.
Very full and on middle, defended.
Tossed up, outside off, straightens up and stays low. Nawaz looks to sweep but misses.
Outside off, guided to third man. Nawaz wants two but settles with one eventually.
Full and slanting on middle. Shakeel prods and blocks.
Good length and on off, Nawaz defends.
On off, Mohammad Nawaz plays it to point.
BEATEN! An expenasive drive to this full one outside off. Nawaz is beaten. Nawaz is not shy in playing his strokes.
Outside off, Nawaz opens the face of the bat and guides it down to third man for one.
Angled into the pads, Saud works it towards mid-wicket for one.
BEATEN! Length and outside off, Nawaz looks to defend but is beaten.
On middle, blocked.
On middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket for one.
Floats it up on off, this is blocked.
On middle, this is kept out.
On middle, this is defended.
On the stumps, this is blocked.
On off, defended.
Shorter and on the body, this is nudged on the leg side.
On the pads, Shakeel works it around the corner for one.
On off, defended.
On off, this is pushed to cover.
FOUR! Well played! This is full and outside off. Nawaz uses his feet and drives it through covers for a boundary. Time for Ben Stokes to think now.
Tossed up on off, tucked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off. Shakeel leans and bunts it to mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up on off. Nawaz prods and keeps it out.
A huge appeal for LBW but looked outside the line. This is full and around off, spinning in. Nawaz steps across to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads.
On off, this time Nawaz connects the sweep to deep square leg. One.
Full and on middle, drilled to mid on for a quick single.
On a length and on off, Shakeel defends it out.
This is full and on middle. Defended out.
This is full, outside off, pushed to cover.
Four! Length and outside off. Shakeel looks to defends, the ball nips away, goes off the outside edge past the slip cordon for a boundary.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket for a single.
On off, kept out.
Outside off, Shakeel steps across and defends.
FOUR! Shakeel now using his feet! Pakistan are running away! Full and outside off. Shakeel drives it through covers for yet another boundary.
In the 90s! Flat and on the pads, nudged to square leg for a single.
That was a chance! On the pads. Nawaz leans to defend, it goes off the inside edge to short leg. The fielder gets his right hand out but fails to hold on. Tough one.
Tossed up on middle. Nawaz looks to sweep but gets a top edge to fine leg for a brace.
On the pads, nudged to square leg.
On a length and outside off. Shakeel defends away from the body.
Too straight on the pads, Shakeel flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Length ball on off, extra bounce. Shakeel defends and gets hit on the gloves.
Lovely back foot punch! Outside off, this is hit through point for one.
On a length and around off. Nawaz steps forward and defends it to mid off.
Shorter and angling in, nudged to square leg for one.
A short one on the body, Mohammad Nawaz ducks under it.
FOUR! Tucked away nice and fine! On the pads, Nawaz flicks it towards fine leg. This one races away to the fence. Just the 65 needed now.
Goes short again, this does not bounce at all. Nawaz ducks, it goes over his body and goes on the bounce to the keeper.

OUT! Gloved and taken! Wood breaks the stand that was taking the game away from England. Still 65 more needed. This is short and on the body, Nawaz looks to pull, he gets in an awkward position to do so as he seems a little cramped up. It goes off the glove and it is taken by Pope. Stokes is elated. They know they are just a wicket away from entering the bowling all-rounders. A good innings from Nawaz. He played with intent but his side would have loved for him to play longer.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Mark Wood

Commentary: Banged in short. Salman lets it go to the keeper.
Another bumper, Agha ducks under it.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Around off, Shakeel opens the face of the bat and guides it towards point for one.
This one comes back in nicely, the line is a little too straight. Agha looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On off, this is blocked.
That is a beauty! Anderson was getting the ball to come back in for some time now but this time he gets it to leave the batter after landing. Salman has a poke at it and gets beaten.

Lovely stuff! That goes just over the off pole. This one comes back in from outside off, Salman first looks to leave but then tries to play it as it comes back in. He is beaten and it goes over the off pole.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! TAKEN! The third umpire feels that is a clean catch and Saud has to walk back! Is that the final nail in the coffin? England are into the bowlers now. It is Wood yet again who does it with the short ball tactic. This is short and down the leg side. Saud looks to pull, this goes off the glove and to Pope who dives and takes it. An appeal. The umpire has a chat with his partner and then takes it upsatirs with the soft signal being out. Replays are difficult to say whether the gloves are under the ball or not and in the end, it is ruled in the favor of the visitors. A superb knock from Saud. He deserved a ton but now walks back.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Mark Wood

Commentary: Bangs it short and on middle, it is ducked under.
Outside off, left alone.

NOT OUT! That is going down leg! England lose a review! Short and on the body. Abrar Ahmed looks to duck but this one does not bounce at all. It hits his body. An appeal but turned down. It is reviewed just in time but replays show that it is going down leg. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Full and on off, it is driven back to Anderson.
First run after the break! Short in length and outside off. Salman dabs it to third man for a single.
FOUR! Feels like Ahmed is not here to block things! On a length and around off. Ahmed swings his bat and hits it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length and on middle. Ahmed swings across, gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Salman steps forward and blocks.
Outside off.  Salman comes down the track to pull but under edges it. The ball rolls just past the off pole.
Short ball on middle. Ahmed pulls it straight to square leg.
FOUR! Hit hard! This is full and around off. Ahmed clears his front leg and hammers it over mid on for another boundary.
Shorter and outside off. Ahmed now tries to dab it away but misses.
FOUR! Placement! If Ahmed plays out a cameo here, England will be in trouble. Length and outside off. Ahmed cuts it very late past short third man for four runs.
FOUR! Multan is finding its voice again! Short ball, around off. Ahmed backs away, opens the face of the bat but it goes off the top edge over short third man for a boundary.
A bouncer and Ahmed sits under it.
Length and on off, nips in. Salman inside edges his push to square leg for one.

OUT! GONE! The little cameo is over! England two wickets away now. Length ball, outside off. Ahmed shuffles in his crease, comes down the track and slaps but it goes off the higher part of the blade and straight in the hands of Ben Duckett at covers. The experienced campaigner gets better of the debutant.
Howout: c Ben Duckett b James Anderson

Commentary: Outside off, blocked to cover.
Length ball, outside off. Zahid Mahmood defends it.
This one stays low on middle. Zahid Mahmood somehow gets bat on it. That would have been plumb if he didn't get his bat there.
Short in length and on off. Zahid Mahmood gets inside the line and blocks.
Goes short, outside off, left alone.
Short ball, outside off. Salman looks to pull, gets an under edge to the keeper on a bounce.
Short ball on middle. Salman is happy to let it go.
Short ball and this is pulled to deep square leg for one.
That looked like going down. Length ball, tailing on the pads. Mahmood misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but the finger stays down. England have one left but they do not waste it.
Length ball on off, Mahmood blocks.
Short in length and outside off. Salman comes down and defends.
On a length and outside off, bit of inward movement. Salman looks to drive but gets an inside edge to square leg.
This one dies off the deck, outside off. Salman looks to defend but misses.
Beaten! Length ball, outside off. Salman looks to defend but misses. The keeper collects and quick under arms it on his stumps. The replay shows Salman just tapped his bat inside the crease.
FOUR! Good shot! Reading the game! Length and outside off. Salman lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
FOUR! 36 needed now! This is going down the wire! Length ball, outside off, Salman pushes it past point, beats Leach's dive and it races into the fence.

OUT! BOWLED! Through the gate! Wood gets his fourth and needs one more to reach the stars! Zahid Mahmood has no answers. Length ball, outside off, again might have hit the cracks. It nips in sharply and beats the inside edge of Mahmood who tries to drive. The ball hits the stumps. Wood is elated.
Howout: b Mark Wood

Commentary: On a length and around off. Ali defends it out.
Wood goes for the full ball on middle. Ali gets his bat down quickly.
A quick bouncer, down leg. Ali lets it go.
A length ball on middle, nips in and keeps low. Ali defends it out again.
Ai survives! Full and slanting on middle. Ali blocks it.
Fuller and on off. Salman prods and defends.
Tossed up, outside off. Defended.
Flighted on middle. Salman leans and defends.
Ali has two balls to survive! On middle, swept behind square leg for one.
Fuller and on off. Ali defends on the front foot.
Fuller ball on middle. Ali survives as he blocks it.
Good length and on off, defended.
Shorter and around off, this is guided through point.
Another one on the shorter side, Salman guides it to point.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! Hit hard and bags a boundary! Fuller and on off, this is hit hard and down to the long off fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! Runs needed now below 30! Shorter and on middle, Salman pulls it over mid-wicket and this one races away to the fence.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Unsurprisingly, Ali takes the review. However, the celebration starts again as the Ultra Edge shows a spike on it. ENGLAND WIN THE SERIES! Ollie Robinson serves a length ball, angling around off and nips away a touch. Ali is drawn forward to defend but gets an edge to the keeper. An appeal and up goes the finger. The review is taken but as expected in vain. England win by 26 runs.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Ollie Robinson
